Kano State Governor, Abdullahi Ganduje, and his anointed successor, Nasir Gawuna, have submitted their Expression of Interest and Nomination forms for Kano North Senatorial District and governorship of the state. The former deputy governor, Abdullahi Gwarzo, who submitted the forms on their behalf, applauded Ganduje over the choice of Gawuna, saying it was in tandem with the wishes of party stakeholders in the state. Flanked by the Commissioner for Information, Mohammed Garba, the former deputy governor said Ganduje deserves the senatorial seat, having served Kano meritoriously in the last seven years.